"input queue is cleared of all older messages before the flush message is "
"delivered. This enables instant interruption in voice pipelines -- when the "
"user speaks over TTS output, the ASR node sends a new segment with `flush: "
"true`, and the TTS node immediately discards any queued audio chunks from "
"the previous response."
