#: src/languages/rust.md:261
msgid "EventStream"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/rust.md:263
msgid ""
"Asynchronous iterator over incoming events destined for this node. "
"Implements the `futures::Stream` trait."
msgstr "此节点传入事件的异步迭代器。实现了 `futures::Stream` trait。"

#: src/languages/rust.md:265
msgid ""
"The event stream closes itself after a `Stop` event is received. Nodes "
"should exit once the stream ends."
msgstr "收到 `Stop` 事件后，事件流会自行关闭。节点应在流结束后退出。"

#: src/languages/rust.md:268
msgid ""
"// Block until the next event arrives. Returns None when the stream closes.\n"
"// Uses an internal EventScheduler that may reorder events for fairness.\n"
msgstr ""
"// 阻塞直到下一个事件到达。流关闭时返回 None。\n"
"// 使用内部 EventScheduler，可能为公平性重新排序事件。\n"

#: src/languages/rust.md:271
msgid "// Block with a timeout. Returns an Event::Error on timeout.\n"
msgstr "// 带超时的阻塞。超时时返回 Event::Error。\n"

#: src/languages/rust.md:274
msgid "// Async receive with EventScheduler reordering.\n"
msgstr "// 带 EventScheduler 重排序的异步接收。\n"

#: src/languages/rust.md:277
msgid "// Async receive with a timeout. Returns Event::Error on timeout.\n"
msgstr "// 带超时的异步接收。超时时返回 Event::Error。\n"

#: src/languages/rust.md:280
msgid ""
"// Non-blocking receive. Returns TryRecvError::Empty if nothing is ready.\n"
msgstr "// 非阻塞接收。无可用数据时返回 TryRecvError::Empty。\n"

#: src/languages/rust.md:283
msgid ""
"// Drain all buffered events without blocking.\n"
"// Returns Some(Vec::new()) if nothing is ready; None if the stream is "
"closed.\n"
msgstr ""
"// 非阻塞地排空所有缓冲事件。\n"
"// 无可用数据时返回 Some(Vec::new())；流关闭时返回 None。\n"

#: src/languages/rust.md:287
msgid "// True if no events are buffered in the scheduler or receiver.\n"
msgstr "// 如果调度器或接收器中没有缓冲事件则为 true。\n"

#: src/languages/rust.md:290
msgid ""
"// Returns and resets accumulated drop counts per input ID.\n"
"// For `drop_oldest` inputs, drops happen at `queue_size`.\n"
"// For `backpressure` inputs, drops happen at 10x `queue_size` (hard safety "
"cap).\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages/rust.md:297
msgid ""
"`EventStream` also implements `futures::Stream<Item = Event>`, so it can be "
"used with `StreamExt::next()` and other combinators. Unlike `recv`/"
"`recv_async`, the `Stream` implementation does **not** use the "
"EventScheduler, preserving chronological event order."
msgstr ""
"`EventStream` 还实现了 `futures::Stream<Item = Event>`，因此可以与 "
"`StreamExt::next()` 和其他组合器一起使用。与 `recv`/`recv_async` 不同，"
"`Stream` 实现**不**使用 EventScheduler，保留事件的时间顺序。"

