#: src/operations/logging.md:1231
msgid "Performance Considerations"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1233
msgid ""
"Logging adds I/O overhead proportional to log volume. Here's how to tune it:"
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1235
msgid ""
"**`min_log_level` is the most impactful setting.** It filters at the daemon "
"before any I/O: no log file write, no coordinator forwarding, no "
"`send_logs_as` routing. A node emitting 1000 debug lines/sec at "
"`min_log_level: info` generates zero overhead for those lines."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1237
msgid ""
"**`send_logs_as` adds a dataflow message per log line.** Each parsed log "
"entry is serialized to JSON, converted to Arrow, and sent through the "
"dataflow. For high-volume nodes, this can consume significant bandwidth. Use "
"`min_log_level` to limit what gets routed."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1239
msgid ""
"**`adora/logs` subscribers share a single serialization.** The daemon "
"converts each log line to Arrow once and clones the result for each "
"subscriber. The cost scales linearly with subscriber count, not log volume x "
"subscriber count. For most dataflows (1-3 log subscribers), this is "
"negligible."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1241
msgid ""
"**Log line size is capped at 1 MB.** Lines longer than 1 MB from node stdout/"
"stderr are truncated to prevent heap exhaustion. This protects against buggy "
"nodes that dump large binary data to stdout."
msgstr ""

#: src/operations/logging.md:1243
msgid ""
"**Log file rotation is recommended for long-running dataflows.** Without "
"`max_log_size`, log files grow unbounded. A node emitting 100 lines/sec at "
"~200 bytes/line fills 1 GB in ~14 hours."
msgstr ""

